<dl id="n35288b"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n35" href="#n35288b">N35 (VI.B.24)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n35all.htm#n35288b"> 288(b)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> Hebdomon / Pege Baluklis / Selivria</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources"><font color="green">[<i>History, Architecture and Antiquities</i>.&mdash;]</font> Of the palaces outside the walls, the most frequented were the palace at the Hebdomon, now Makrikeui, in the early days of the Empire, and the palace of the Peg&eacute;, now Balukli, a short distance beyond the gate of Selivria, in later times. <small> &ldquo;CONSTANTINOPLE&rdquo; <cite a>Encyclopaedia Britannica</cite></a>, 11th edit. (1911) 6</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
